class_name RoomLayouts
extends Object
## Hand-designed room layouts, as ASCII.
##
## Why ASCII: a TileMapLayer stores its cells as an opaque PackedInt32Array, which
## is unreadable and unreviewable in a diff. These maps are the source of truth —
## edit them here and re-run tools/gen_rooms.gd. The generated .tscn files are
## still ordinary Godot scenes you can open and edit; if you do, edit them here
## too or the next regen will overwrite you.
##
## Legend:
##   #  solid tile
##   =  one-way platform (jump up through it, land on top)
##   .  empty
##   P  player entry
##   X  exit
##   g  grunt spawn    b  brute spawn    d  dart spawn
##
## Design budget: the player's jump rises 109 px = 3.4 tiles, so a step of 3
## tiles is comfortable and 4 is impossible. Horizontal reach at full speed is
## ~218 px = 6.8 tiles, so a 6-tile gap is a committed jump and 7 will not make it.
## Every gap below is <= 6.
##
## Rooms are 58x18 playable; the generator adds a 1-tile border, giving 60x20
## tiles = 1920x640 px, matching the fixed camera used everywhere else.

const WIDTH: int = 58
const HEIGHT: int = 18

## Entry room. Deliberately gentle: somewhere to land, a couple of ledges to
